//Linux Commands
Linux Commands:-


pwd         Present working directors

mkdir      "naem"   make new folder

cd            Change DIrectory

ls            (LIst all files)

ls -R        (Subdirectories)

ls -a         (hidden files)

cat>filename           (Creates new file & add content simultaneously in one go)

cat filename            (Shows contents of filename)

Ctrl+D                        (Exits when inside a file.)

cat file1 file2>file3           (concatenates file1+file2 into file3)

cat>>filename                       ( Points cursor to the end of existing file )

act filename|tr a-z A-Z            (converts filename's contents to uppercase)

act filename|tr A-Z a-z             (converts filename's contents to lowercase)
rm file3                                         (to remove file)

touch filename                           (creates new blank file)

head -n 3 filename              (shows first 3 lines fo filename)

tail  -n 3 filename                (shows last 3 lines fo filename)

wc  filename             (Lines , words, Letters and FIlename)

wc -l filename                       (tells number of lines in filename)
wc -L filename                       (Length of longest line in filename)

wc -w filename                 (tells number of words in filename)

cal                                      (Prints Date if ncal library installed)

cal 1 2022                       (Prints  Calendar of January 2022)

diff file1 file2                (Prints Difference of file1 file2)

rmdir                                (delete empty directory)

rmdir -r
